The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring the third Saturday of each May as Armed Forces Day in the United States. The proclamation recognizes and pays tribute to the men and women of the armed forces who risk their lives to defend the nation and its freedoms. It emphasizes the importance of supporting and providing for military personnel, including their families, and encourages Americans to display the flag at their homes and volunteer at organizations that support troops. The proclamation also calls upon civil authorities, private citizens, governors, and organizations to participate in observances and increase public understanding and appreciation of the armed forces.